{
	"mim_type": "announcement",
	"rule_name": "",
	"timeout": 6,
	"barge_in": true,
	"es_auto_tagging": false,
	"notes": "Turn off embodied speech.",
	"prompts": [
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-1\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. It seems like you were looking somewhere else, maybe at another person, or a pet, or a U F O. It would help if you could look directly at my screen a bit longer. <break size='0.3'/>Here we go, starting now.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_01",
			"weight": 0.3
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-0\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I'm not seeing anyone. It might be low light, or you're far away, or you're moving. Make sure you can see yourself in the viewfinder, and stand about an arm's length away.<break size='0.3'/> Let's pick up from where we left off.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_02",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-2\" ",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. Either I'm seeing double, or there are two people standing in front of me. For now, let me look at only ${loopMember}. <break size='0.3'/>Let's try it again.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_03",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-3\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I see three faces right now. It would be good if I only saw ${loopMember} for now. <break size='0.3'/>Let's try it again, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_04",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-4\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I see four faces right now. I really need to just see ${loopMember} for this to work. <break size='0.3'/>I'll pick up where we left off, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_05",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-5\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I think I see five people around. I'd much rather see just ${loopMember} for now, not because I don't like groups of five, but because I'm trying to learn a face.<break size='0.3'/> I'll try again, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_06",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-many\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I'm seeing a lot of people here right now. Really it would be ideal if I was looking only at ${loopMember}. <break size='0.3'/>I'll pick up where we left off, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_07",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-1\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I think you were looking off to the side. It'd be great if you would stare right at me. <break size='0.3'/>Let's get back at it, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_08",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-1\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I think you were looking away. I don't take it personally, but I do need to see your face straight on, to learn it.<break size='0.3'/> Let's try again.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_09",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-0\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I'm not seeing you. It could be because it's bad lighting, or you're moving, or too far away. Be sure you can see yourself on my screen, and stand about an arm's length away. <break size='0.3'/>Let's try again, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_10",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-0\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I don't see anyone at all. It might be a little dark in here, or you're moving, or you're too far away from me, or you slipped into another dimension, really it's hard for me to tell. Position yourself in my viewfinder, and we'll try this again.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_11",
			"weight": 0.2
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-2\" ",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I'm seeing two faces. ${loopMember} assuming you don't have two faces, please make sure you're the only one standing in front of me. <break size='0.3'/>Here we go.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_12",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-3\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. There are three faces in my view at the moment, and I really need to just see ${loopMember}. I'll start again. <break size='0.3'/> Ready, and, now.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_13",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-3\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. ${loopMember} either you have three faces, or there are a couple of other people standing near you. It'd be much better if it was only you there. Let's try again, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_14",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-3\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I see three faces, which is about two too many. It would be great if I could look at just ${loopMember} right now. <break size='0.3'/>Starting again, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_15",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-4\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I'm seeing four faces. I'd have a much easier time if it was just ${loopMember} for now. <break size='0.3'/>I'll start again, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_16",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-4\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. Unless I'm mistaken, which I admit is very possible, there are four faces in front of me. Things will go much smoother if it's just ${loopMember}. <break size='0.3'/>I'll try again, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_17",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-5\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I see five people right now. A great number for a basketball team, but not so good for face recognition. How bout I just see ${loopMember} for now. <break size='0.3'/> I'll try again, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_18",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-5\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I'm either looking at five faces, or a five-headed monster. Either way, it'd be great if it could be just ${loopMember} in front of me instead. <break size='0.3'/>Let's try this again.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_19",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-many\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. It seems like a lot of people are gathered around you, or maybe you've set up an elaborate system of mirrors. Either way, it would help me a lot if only ${loopMember} were framed in my viewfinder. <break size='0.3'/>Okay here we go, trying again.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_20",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-many\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I think I see a group of people around. I'd much rather see just ${loopMember} for now, not because I don't like groups, but because I'm trying to learn a face. <break size='0.3'/>I'll try again, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error1_AN_21",
			"weight": 1
		}
	],
	"gui": null,
	"no_matches_for_gui": 2,
	"no_inputs_for_gui": 2,
	"ignore_no_match": false,
	"parse_all_asr": false,
	"thanks_handling": "ignore",
	"parse_launch": false
